[It is not clear if these cases are laboratory confirmed or suspected cases of chikungunya virus infection based on clinical signs. Severe arthralgia, not mentioned in the report above, can persist in individuals weeks or months following the acute phase of the infection. There have been sporadic epidemics of chikungunya virus infections in the Philippines in 1954, 1956, 1968, and 1985 to 1986 (see ProMED-mail archive no 20120929.1315954).

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of the Philippines can be seen at http://healthmap.org/r/3AV9. A map showing the location of Albay province can be accessed at http://philippinemaps.ph/Philippines-Maps/Philippine-401-regions_provinces.png and Rapu-Rapu municipality can be seen on the map at http://www.zamboanga.com/z/images/d/d3/Albay_rapu-rapu.png. - Mod.TY]
